Visualizing time series data

Mahbubul Majumder, PhD
April 11, 2017

Time series data

dat <- read.csv("co2emission.csv")
ggplot(dat, aes(YearMonth, CO2)) + geom_line() + 
  geom_smooth(method=loess, se=FALSE)

Detrending the data

library(modelr)
fit <- lm(CO2~YearMonth, data=dat)
dDat <- dat %>%
  add_residuals(fit)
ggplot(dDat, aes(YearMonth, resid)) + geom_line() + 
  geom_smooth(method=loess, se=FALSE)

  • the trend line is CO2 = - 2537 + 1.452 * YearMonth

Seasonal variation

lag.plot(dDat$resid, lags=12)

Autocorrelation

acf(dDat$resid)

Moving averages

Decomposition

tSeries <- ts(dDat$CO2, frequency=12, start=c(1974,5))
dcomposedDat <- decompose(tSeries)
plot(dcomposedDat)

Fitting the best ARIMA

library(forecast)
tModel <- auto.arima(tSeries)
summary(tModel)

Showing fitted model

dDat$ts <- fitted(tModel)
mDat <- dDat[,c(2,1,8)] %>% melt(id="YearMonth")
ggplot(mDat, aes(YearMonth, value, color=variable)) + 
  geom_line() + geom_point(aes(YearMonth, value), data=subset(mDat, variable=="ts"))

Showing forcasted values

plot(forecast(tModel))

Diagnostics of residual

acf(resid(tModel))

Diagnostics of residual

qplot(fitted(tModel), resid(tModel), geom="point")

Case Study: Boston armed robbery

dRobbery <- read.csv("boston-armed-robberies.csv")
tRobbery <- ts(dRobbery$armed.robberies, 
               start = c(1966,1), frequency = 12)
plot(tRobbery)

Log transformation to stabilize variance

tRobbery <- ts(log(dRobbery$armed.robberies), 
               start = c(1966,1), frequency = 12)
plot(tRobbery)

Find the best ARIMA model

rModel <- auto.arima(tRobbery)
summary(rModel)

Series: tRobbery 
ARIMA(1,1,1)(0,0,1)[12] with drift         

Coefficients:
         ar1      ma1    sma1   drift
      0.5893  -0.9384  0.1482  0.0213
s.e.  0.1333   0.0817  0.0975  0.0034

sigma^2 estimated as 0.03613:  log likelihood=29.74
AIC=-49.49   AICc=-48.95   BIC=-35.68

Training set error measures:
                        ME      RMSE       MAE       MPE     MAPE
Training set -0.0004286504 0.1860002 0.1486117 -0.106551 3.093125
                  MASE        ACF1
Training set 0.4458498 -0.03714693

Fitted model: ARIMA(1,1,1)

  • Autoregressive AR(1) model: \( Y_t = \phi Y_{t-1} + e_t \)

  • Moving Average MA(1) model : \( Y_t = e_t + \theta e_{t-1} \)

  • Integrated I(1) model:

    • take first difference \( Y_t - Y_{t-1} \)
    • this transformation makes the series stationary

  • ARI(1,1) model: \( Y_t - Y_{t-1} = \phi (Y_{t-1}- Y_{t-2}) + e_t \)

  • Final model: ARIMA(1,1,1)

\[ Y_t - Y_{t-1} = \phi (Y_{t-1}- Y_{t-2}) + e_t + \theta e_{t-1} \]

or

\[ Y_t = (1+\phi) Y_{t-1} - \phi Y_{t-2} + e_t + \theta e_{t-1} \]

Residual diagnosis

qplot(fitted(rModel), resid(rModel))

Residual diagnosis

acf(resid(rModel))

Fitted robberies vs Actual

plot(tRobbery) ; lines(fitted(rModel), col="red")

Fitted robberies vs Actual (original scale)

plot(exp(tRobbery)) ; lines(exp(fitted(rModel)), col="red")

Showing forecasted values

fCast <- forecast(rModel)
plot(fCast)

Showing forecasted values in original scale

fTime <- seq(1975.833,length=24, by=1/12)

fDat <- data.frame(date=c(time(tRobbery), fTime),
                   actual = c(exp(tRobbery), rep(NA, 24)),
                   fitted = c(exp(fitted(rModel)), rep(NA, 24)),
                   forcasted = c(rep(NA, 118), exp(fCast$mean)))

mdat <- melt(fDat, id="date")

fRange <- data.frame(date = fTime,
                     lower = exp(fCast$lower[,2]),
                     upper = exp(fCast$upper[,2]))

Showing forecasted values

ggplot(mdat) + geom_line(aes(date, value, color=variable)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(x= date, ymin = lower, ymax = upper), 
              fill = "blue", data=fRange, alpha=0.3)
